# Inbound share product principle

**Goal:** Reduce friction from “found a place” → “on the trip plan” to the fewest taps, using apps users already use (Google Maps, Apple Maps, Safari, Messages).

## North star

> Share from anywhere → Triftly appears in the system share row → user lands in **Add Spot** with name/address prefilled → slide to save.

Supports onboarding pillars: **easy plan creation**, **easy fill-up**, **easy sharing**, **one datasource for buddies** (spot syncs to cloud trip).

## UX rules (do not regress)

1. **Never dead-end** — if parsing fails, still open Add Spot with the raw URL/text in the address field.
2. **Trip selection** — count editable trips (owner / edit role, not mock):
   - **Exactly one** → auto-select that trip, navigate to trip detail, open Add Spot prefilled.
   - **Two or more** → show **`SharedPlaceTripPickerSheet`** (bottom sheet) on the current screen; user picks trip → then navigate + Add Spot.
   - **Zero** → snackbar: create a trip first.
3. **Preserve context** — prefill **name** + **address**; user only confirms day/category if needed.
4. **Read-only trips** — skip joined viewer trips in the picker; explain if nothing is editable.
5. **No Google partnership required** — iOS Share Extension + URL/text parsing; no Maps SDK for inbound share.

## Technical pattern

| Layer | Responsibility |
|--------|----------------|
| `TriftlyShare` (iOS) / `ACTION_SEND` (Android) | Receive URL or plain text from share sheet |
| `app/share` MethodChannel | Hand off payload to Flutter (`getPendingSharedUrl`) |
| `SharedMapParser` | Extract name, address, lat/lng from Maps URLs and share text |
| `SharedPlaceFlow` | Pending place + armed trip id for Add Spot |
| `SharedPlaceListener` | Poll on launch/resume; show trip picker; **`go`** to trip detail (not `push` on shell routes) |
| `AddSpotBottomSheet` | `initialName` / `initialAddress` from shared place |
| `inbound_debug_log.dart` | Debug tracing — filter console with `📍 SHARE` or `[triftly.share]` |

## iOS share extension

- Activation: `public.url`, `public.plain-text`, web URLs (Google Maps shares).
- Open main app via `extensionContext?.open(triftly://map?url=…)` — **not** `UIApplication` from extension.
- User may need **Edit Actions → enable Triftly** once (iOS share sheet discovery).

## Parsing expectations

| Input | Extract |
|-------|---------|
| `google.com/maps/place/Name/@lat,lng` | Name, coordinates, maps URL as address |
| `maps.google.com/?q=…` | Query or coordinates |
| Plain text `Place · City\nhttps://maps…` | Title line + URL |
| Unrecognized | Raw string → address field |

## Out of scope (later phases)

- Short-link expansion (`goo.gl` / `maps.app.goo.gl`) without network
- Share extension UI to pick trip before opening app (App Group)
- Android share target manifest parity beyond `ACTION_SEND`
- Auto-assign day (default: current plan day in trip detail)

