## Debug logging

Filter Xcode / `flutter run` with **`📍 SHARE`** or **`[triftly.share]`** (same pattern as `🔐 AUTH` / `[triftly.auth]`).

| Glyph | Meaning |
|-------|---------|
| 🔗 | Deep link received (map URL, trip share token) |
| 📱 | iOS native bridge (`app/share`) |
| 🔍 | Parsed place payload |
| 🧭 | Router / navigator state |
| ✈️ | Flow decisions (picker, auto-select, queue) |
| ⏭️ | Duplicate suppressed |
| ✅ | Add Spot opened |
| ❌ | Error |

Example lines:

```
📍 SHARE 🔗 │ Map deep link (router) — staged → Test · … · fallback=/plan
📍 SHARE 📱 │ iOS onSharedUrlReady — polling Flutter
📍 SHARE ✈️ │ Single trip auto-select → Tokyo 2026 (abc-123)
📍 SHARE ✅ │ Opening Add Spot sheet → tripId=abc-123 · Test · …
```
